Data Visualization¶

Histograms¶

In [60]:
import plotly as py
import plotly.graph_objs as go
from plotly import tools
from plotly.offline import download_plotlyjs, init_notebook_mode, plot, iplot
import ipywidgets as widgets
import numpy as np
init_notebook_mode(connected=True)

def plot_histograms(bins):
    figHists = tools.make_subplots(rows=3, cols=4)
    counter = 0
    for row in range(3):
        for col in range(4):
            hist = go.Histogram(x = df_data.iloc[::10, counter], 
                                name = df_data.columns.values[counter],
                                nbinsx = bins
                               )

            figHists.append_trace(hist, row+1, col+1)

            counter += 1
            if counter == 11:
                break
    layout = go.Layout(bargap=0.1)
    fig = go.Figure(data=figHists, layout=layout)
    py.offline.iplot(fig)

bin_slider = widgets.IntSlider(value=30, min=3, max=50, step=1)
_=widgets.interact(plot_histograms, bins=bin_slider)

UMAP (Dimension reduction)¶

In [63]:
import umap

def umap_dimension_reduction(data):
    embedding = umap.UMAP(n_neighbors=10, min_dist=0.1,
    metric='correlation').fit_transform(data)

    colorsIdx = {'OK': '#d95f0e', 'Failure': '#bcbddc'}

    cols = df_data['class'].map(colorsIdx)

    trace = go.Scatter(x=embedding[:, 0],
    y=embedding[:, 1],
    mode='markers',
    marker=dict(size=4, color=cols, opacity=0.8))
    data = [trace]
    py.offline.iplot(data, filename='basic-scatter')


umap_dimension_reduction(df_data.iloc[:, :-1].dropna())

Creating and Validating Prediction Model¶

Train and Visualise a Decision Tree Classification Model¶

In [66]:
from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier, export_graphviz
from sklearn import tree
from IPython.display import SVG
from graphviz import Source
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split

def build_decision_tree(max_depth, min_samples_leaf):
    DecisionTree = DecisionTreeClassifier(criterion = 'entropy',
                                          random_state = 0,
                                          max_depth = max_depth,
                                          min_samples_leaf = min_samples_leaf)

    X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(df_data_enc.iloc[:, :-1],
                                                        df_data_enc.iloc[:, -1],
                                                        test_size = 0.9,
                                                        random_state = 100)
    print(type(y_train), type(y_test), y_test.unique())
    DecisionTree.fit(X = X_train, 
                     y = y_train.astype(bool)) #.astype(int)

    labels = df_data.iloc[:, :-1].columns.values
    graph = Source(tree.export_graphviz(DecisionTree,
                                        out_file = None,
                                        feature_names = labels,
                                        class_names = ['OK', 'Failure'],
                                        filled = True))

    display(SVG(graph.pipe(format='svg')))

depth_slider = widgets.IntSlider(value=2, min=1, max=10, step=1)
sample_slider = widgets.IntSlider(value=100, min=1, max=500, step=1)
_=widgets.interact(build_decision_tree, 
                 max_depth = depth_slider, 
                 min_samples_leaf = sample_slider)

Model validation¶

In [67]:
from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix
from sklearn.metrics import classification_report


def build_confusion_matrix(max_depth, min_samples_leaf, training_set_size):
    DecisionTree = DecisionTreeClassifier(criterion='entropy',
                                          random_state=0,
                                          max_depth=max_depth,
                                          min_samples_leaf=min_samples_leaf)

    X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(
        df_data_enc.iloc[:, :-1],
        df_data_enc.iloc[:, -1],
        test_size=(1 - training_set_size),
        random_state=100)
    DecisionTree.fit(X=X_train, y=y_train.astype(int))

    y_pred = DecisionTree.predict(X_test)
    cm = confusion_matrix(y_test.astype(int), y_pred)

    cm_text = [[
        '<b>False Positive:<br />' + str(cm[1, 0]) + '</b>',
        '<b>True Negative:<br />' + str(cm[1, 1]) + '</b>'
    ],
               [
                   '<b>True Positive:<br />' + str(cm[0, 0]) + '</b>',
                   '<b>False Negative:<br />' + str(cm[0, 1]) + '</b>'
               ]]


    precision = np.round(cm[0, 0] / (cm[0, 0] + cm[1, 0]), decimals=3) * 100
    recall = np.round(cm[0, 0] / (cm[0, 0] + cm[0, 1]), decimals=4) * 100
    acc = np.round(
        (cm[0, 0] + cm[1, 1]) / (cm[0, 0] + cm[0, 1] + cm[1, 0] + cm[1, 1]),
        decimals=4) * 100

    table_data = [[' ', '<b>Predicted class: OK</b>', '<b>Predicted class: Failure</b>',' '],
                  ['<b>Actual class: OK</b>', cm[0, 0], cm[0, 1],'<b>Recall =\n' + str(recall) + "%</b>"], 
                  ['<b>Actual class: Failure</b>', cm[1, 0], cm[1, 1], ' '],
                  [' ', '<b>Precision =\n' + str(precision) + "%</b>", ' ', '<b>Accuracy = \n' + str(acc) + "%</b>"
                  ]]

    table = ff.create_table(table_data, height_constant=60)
    py.offline.iplot(table)


depth_slider = widgets.IntSlider(value=2, min=1, max=10, step=1)
sample_slider = widgets.IntSlider(value=100, min=1, max=500, step=1)
training_set_slider = slider = widgets.FloatSlider(value=0.8,
                                                   min=0.01,
                                                   max=1,
                                                   step=0.01)

build_confusion_matrix(10, 10, 0.3)
